<table border=0 cellspacing=1 cellpadding=1>
	<tr>
		<td valign=middle align=left width=22><IMG src="/help/images/clear.gif" height=1 width=20 border=0></td>
		<td valign=middle align=right class="header">Quick Messages</td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2"><hr size="1"></td></tr>
	<tr>
    <td valign=top align=left colspan="2" class="text">The Quick messenger portlet 
      allows users to see other online and offline users and enables them to send 
      quick messages to those users.</td>
  </tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2" class="text"><IMG src="/help/images/clear.gif" height=5 width=1 border=0></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2" class="subheader">To Send A Quick Message</td></tr>
    <tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">1.</td>
		
    <td valign=top align=left class="text">Under the <em>Quick Messenger</em> 
      portlet, select the online or offline users.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">2.</td>
		
    <td valign=top align=left class="text">A small pop-up window will appear. 
      Type in the message and click on the <strong>Send</strong> button.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">3.</td>
		
    <td valign=top align=left class="text">On the recipient's side, a new quick 
      message (maximum listing of 5) will appear under the <em>Incoming Quick 
      Messages</em> showing the date, the time and the sender's name.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">4.</td>
		
    <td valign=top align=left class="text">Click on the link to read the quick 
      message. To reply the quick message, type in the message and click on the 
      <strong>Send</strong> button.</td>
	</tr>
</table>
